            <thetext>Analyzer ignores any file without a &quot;.&quot;, this happened as part of fixing bug 153.

While i agree that indexing binaries accidentally as zip files should be avoided, not indexing Makefiles is a showstopper for many deployments. Perhaps suffixes for files that are explicitly expected to have &quot;.&quot; in them (.cpp, .zip, etc.) should include the &quot;.&quot;, while suffixes expected to match whole filenames (Makefile, configure, SConstruct) can be included plainly.

I&apos;ll whip up a patch for review.</thetext>
